    <note>Tan(3) Shiji [17308] Hunan TZ, 134.13a has jinshi in Chongning (year unk.). When Shiji held office in the imperial library, Cai(1) Jing's [1649] son was chief librarian (Ling shuju), and those in office here all tried to seek high position. Shiji remained in the same position for six years without a promotion. He memorialized several times about poor government. He held office in the same burueau as Xu(4) Han [8062], which Han uses to explain his reason for drafting the funerary inscription for Shiji's mother, wife of Zhang [3816] (q.v.). CBD, 5, 4260.</note>
